Sentencas: We here report a lanthanum ferrite-based perovskite anode La0.9Ca0.1Fe1-xNbxO3-delta (LCFNbx, x = 0, 0.05, 0.1 and 0.2) for solid oxide fuel cells (SOFCs) with intriguing stability and electrochemical performance.
Titulo: Stability and electrochemical performance of lanthanum ferrite-based composite SOFC anodes in hydrogen and carbon monoxide
